Two French experts are to provide training on  airport security and fighting the narcotics trade, a French embassy statement  said here Thursday.
Experts Florent Humbert and Alain Labro will provide two weeks of training  to 25 Bangladeshi police, customs, narcotics and civil aviation authority  officials, the embassy said.
The Paris-based International Department of Technical Police Cooperation  and the Bangladesh Civil Aviation Authority are jointly organising the  programme, which starts next week.
International drug and gold smuggling rings frequent Dhaka's Zia  International Airport, officials said.
